Conda build needs to take additional options to fully support the binstar upload feature.  For automated builds, it should take a --token and --private,--personal,--public option.  Otherwise, one needs to run conda build with --no-binstar-upload while building, and then again with --output to get the filename. 

The following should be one command:
```
/opt/anaconda/bin/conda build ${WORKSPACE}/${project} --no-binstar-upload
package=`/opt/anaconda/bin/conda build ${WORKSPACE}/${project} --output`
binstar -t ${TOKEN} upload --private ${package}
```

